cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL

The paper deals with game theory and graph algorithms, which are common topics in the cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of infinite memory in optimal strategies suggests a connection to the cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexity of solving the game, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the use of effective constructions for optimal strategies suggests a connection to the cs.PL (Programming Languages) sub-category.
